ozhium-ollium Dependencies
===========================

Build Dependencies
-------------------
  - GCC or Clang compiler
  - pkg-config
  - make
  - libpulse-dev     (PulseAudio C API — used even with PipeWire via pipewire-pulse)
  - libmnl-dev       (netlink library for network/bluetooth/VPN events)
  - libudev-dev      (udev for hardware event detection)

Runtime Dependencies
--------------------
  Audio server (choose one):
    - pulseaudio                 (PulseAudio sound server)
    - pipewire + pipewire-pulse  (PipeWire with PulseAudio compat layer)

  UI (ozhium-ollium-ui) — choose one backend:
    - Option A (GTK):  gtk4, gtk4-layer-shell
    - Option B (Qt):   qt6-base, qt6-declarative

System Requirements
-------------------
  - Linux kernel with inotify and netlink support
  - PulseAudio sound server (or pipewire-pulse for PipeWire)
  - /sys/class/backlight/    (backlight device paths)
  - /sys/class/power_supply/ (battery device paths)

Installation Examples
---------------------

### Ubuntu/Debian

**Daemon (build deps):**
  sudo apt install build-essential pkg-config libpulse-dev libmnl-dev libudev-dev

**Runtime audio server — choose one:**
  sudo apt install pulseaudio                    # PulseAudio
  sudo apt install pipewire pipewire-pulse       # PipeWire

**UI — GTK4 backend:**
  sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev libgtk4-layer-shell-dev

**UI — Qt6 backend:**
  sudo apt install qt6-base-dev qt6-declarative-dev

### Fedora/RHEL

**Daemon (build deps):**
  sudo dnf install gcc make pkg-config pulseaudio-libs-devel libmnl-devel systemd-devel

**Runtime audio server — choose one:**
  sudo dnf install pulseaudio                        # PulseAudio
  sudo dnf install pipewire pipewire-pulseaudio      # PipeWire

**UI — GTK4 backend:**
  sudo dnf install gtk4-devel gtk4-layer-shell-devel

**UI — Qt6 backend:**
  sudo dnf install qt6-qtbase-devel qt6-qtdeclarative-devel

### Arch Linux

**Daemon (build deps):**
  sudo pacman -S base-devel pkgconf pulseaudio libmnl

**Runtime audio server — choose one:**
  sudo pacman -S pulseaudio                  # PulseAudio
  sudo pacman -S pipewire pipewire-pulse     # PipeWire

**UI — GTK4 backend:**
  sudo pacman -S gtk4 gtk4-layer-shell

**UI — Qt6 backend:**
  sudo pacman -S qt6-base qt6-declarative

### openSUSE

**Daemon (build deps):**
  sudo zypper install gcc make pkg-config libpulse-devel libmnl-devel

**Runtime audio server — choose one:**
  sudo zypper install pulseaudio                  # PulseAudio
  sudo zypper install pipewire pipewire-pulseaudio # PipeWire

**UI — GTK4 backend:**
  sudo zypper install gtk4-devel gtk4-layer-shell-devel

**UI — Qt6 backend:**
  sudo zypper install qt6-base-devel qt6-declarative-devel

Verification
------------
  After installation, run:
    make

  This will build both:
    - ozhium-ollium      (daemon)
    - ozhium-ollium-ui  (UI binary)
